`crates/steno/src` is the compiler crate for `.steno` dictionary source: a strictly forward pipeline (parse → expand → render/snippet) plus supporting subsystems (stroke encoding, editor keystroke simulation, error types, JSON output) that the pipeline and its consuming binaries depend on. Depending on this crate gets you `lib.rs`'s public API — `expand_dict`, `build_plain_dict`/`build_smart_dict`, snippet builders — never direct file I/O; all output-writing is left to `bin/`.

The pipeline stages are strict producer/consumer contracts: `parse/` emits `Entry`/`Chunk`, `expand/` resolves those into `TypedEntry` through its own three-pass sequence, and `render/`+`snippet/` are the two terminal consumers of `TypedEntry`, differing only in target format (Plover dict text vs. LSP snippet bodies) and both routing profile behavior through `editor/`'s `Behaviors` constants (`PLAIN`/`SMART`). A change to `editor::PLAIN`/`SMART` silently changes both `render/` and (via `blocks.rs`) auto-indent emission with no corresponding edit in those consumers — the crate's sharpest cross-module risk. `stroke/` underlies both `expand/` (count-bank arithmetic) and `render/`/`snippet/` (stroke text in output), so its canonical key ordering and re-formatting-not-preserving behavior surfaces everywhere strokes are touched.

`error.rs` defines the one typed-error family (`StrokeError`, `StenoError`, `ExpandError`, `RenderError`, `SnippetError`) that every stage returns instead of panicking — a crate-wide invariant, no panics on malformed input, enforced independently in `parse/`, `expand/`, `render/`, and `stroke/`. `json_out.rs` is a leaf utility (byte-identical `JSON.stringify` reproduction) consumed by `snippet/build.rs` and the `bin/` binaries for deterministic output ordering. `blocks.rs` is a render-adjacent leaf: it emits `editor::Event` keystrokes for `@literal` blocks specifically, independent of the main `render/`/`snippet/` template path.

No intent.md exists for this directory.